30/10/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The European Commission Ambassador to Skopje, Erwan Fouere, expects talks on liberalising the EU visa regime for Macedonian citizens to begin shortly. 
Quoted in the Albanian-language weekly National, Fouere also said he anticipates the EU visa regime to be eased soon for certain categories, such as students and members of the business community.
In other news, Macedonian Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski said on Friday (October 27th) that receiving a concrete date for starting EU membership negotiations would be a main objective of his government next year. 
His comment followed an informal meeting with German President Horst Koehler in Berlin, in which Gruevski sought German support on this issue. 
(Makfax - 30/10/06; Vecer - 28/10/06; A1 TV - 27/10/06)
